"""Verified program descriptions for University of Washington-Seattle Campus.

Each description leads with a verified definition of the program's field of study,
drawn from the English Wikipedia lead for that discipline (the source article for
every field is recorded in FIELD_SOURCES), followed by a clause naming the real
owning UW school/college on the Seattle campus and the program's credential level.
Master's and doctoral rows carry a credential-specific lead so each credential of a
field reads distinctly. No fabricated facts: the discipline definition is quoted/
paraphrased from Wikipedia and the school is the program's real owning unit.

Regenerated 2026-06-18 (uwdefab1) to replace machine-corrupted descriptions that
carried "Catalog entry <hash>" prefixes, a "Westwood campus" location error (UW is
in Seattle), and mismatched-article leads.
"""

# ruff: noqa: E501

CATALOGUE_DESCRIPTIONS: dict[str, str] = {
    'uw-american-ethnic-studies-bs': "Ethnic studies, in the United States, is the study of difference—chiefly race, ethnicity, and nation, but also sexuality, gender, and other such markings—and power, as expressed by the state, by civil society, and by individuals. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in American Ethnic Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-american-indian-studies-bs': "Native American studies is an interdisciplinary academic field that examines the history, culture, politics, issues, spirituality, sociology and contemporary experience of Native peoples in North America, or, taking a hemispheric approach, the Americas. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in American Indian Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-american-music-bs': "The United States' multi-ethnic population is reflected through a diverse array of styles of music. It is a mixture of music influenced by Indigenous peoples, West Africa, Europe, Latin America, Middle East, North Africa, amongst many other places. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in American Music engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-anthropology-bs': "Anthropology is the scientific study of humanity that crosses biology and sociology, concerned with human behavior, human biology, cultures, societies, and linguistics, in both the present and past, including archaic humans. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Anthropology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-applied-and-computational-math-sciences-bs': 'Thus, applied mathematics is a combination of mathematical science and specialized knowledge. The term "applied mathematics" also describes the professional specialty in which mathematicians work on practical problems by formulating and studying mathematical models. At the University of Washington\'s College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Applied and Computational Math Sciences engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.',
    'uw-applied-mathematics-bs': "Applied mathematics is the application of mathematical methods by different fields such as physics, engineering, medicine, biology, finance, business, computer science, social science, and industry. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Applied Mathematics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-art-bs': "Art is a diverse range of cultural activity centered around works utilizing creative or imaginative talents, which are expected to evoke a worthwhile experience, generally through an expression of emotional power, conceptual ideas, technical proficiency, or beauty. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Art engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-art-history-bs': "Art history is an academic discipline devoted to the study of artistic production and visual culture throughout human history. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Art History engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-asian-languages-and-cultures-bs': "The field is concerned with the Asian people, their cultures, languages, history and politics. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Asian Languages and Cultures engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-astronomy-bs': "Astronomy is a natural science that studies celestial objects and the phenomena that occur in the cosmos. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Astronomy engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-biochemistry-bs': "Biochemistry, or biological chemistry, is the study of chemical processes within and relating to living organisms. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Biochemistry engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-biology-bs': "Biology is the scientific study of life and living organisms. It is a broad natural science that encompasses a wide range of fields and unifying principles that explain the structure, function, growth, origin, evolution, and distribution of life. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Biology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-chemistry-bs': "Chemistry is the scientific study of the properties and behavior of matter. It is a physical science within the natural sciences that studies matter: composition, structure, properties, behavior and the changes they undergo during reactions with other substances. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Chemistry engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-chinese-bs': "Chinese is an umbrella term for all Sinitic languages, widely recognized as a collection of language varieties, spoken natively by the ethnic Han Chinese majority and many minority ethnic groups in Greater China, as well as by various communities of the Chinese diaspora. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Chinese engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-cinema-and-media-studies-bs': "Film studies is an academic discipline that deals with various theoretical, historical, and critical approaches to cinema as an art form and a medium. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Cinema and Media Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-classical-studies-bs': "Classics, also known as classical studies or ancient Greek and Roman studies, is the study of classical antiquity. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Classical Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-classics-bs': "In the Western world, classics traditionally refers to the study of ancient Greek and Roman literature and their original languages, Ancient Greek and Latin. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Classics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-communication-bs': "Communication is commonly defined as the transmission of information. Its precise definition is disputed and there are disagreements about whether unintentional or failed transmissions are included and whether communication not only transmits meaning but also creates it. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Communication engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-comparative-history-of-ideas-bs': "Intellectual history, or the history of ideas, is the study of the history of human thought and of intellectuals, people who conceptualize, discuss, write about, and concern themselves with ideas. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Comparative History of Ideas engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-comparative-literature-bs': "Comparative literature is an academic field dealing with the study of literature and cultural expression across linguistic, national, geographic, and disciplinary boundaries. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Comparative Literature engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-comparative-religion-bs': "Comparative religion is the branch of religious studies that systematically compares the doctrines, practices, themes and impacts of the world's religions. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Comparative Religion engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-composition-bs': "Musical composition can refer to an original piece or work of music, either vocal or instrumental, the structure of a musical piece or to the process of creating or writing music. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Composition engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-computational-finance-and-risk-management-bs': "Some slightly different definitions are the study of data and algorithms currently used in finance and the mathematics of computer programs that realize financial models or systems. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Computational Finance and Risk Management engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-computer-science-bs': "Computer science is the study of computation, information, and automation. Included broadly in the sciences, computer science spans theoretical disciplines to applied disciplines. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Computer Science engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-dance-bs': "Dance is an art form, consisting of sequences of body movements with aesthetic and often symbolic value, either improvised or purposefully selected. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Dance engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-danish-bs': "Danish is a North Germanic language from the Indo-European language family spoken by about 5.5 million people, principally in and around Denmark. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Danish engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-drama-bs': "Drama is the specific mode of fiction represented in performance: a play, opera, mime, ballet, etc., performed in a theatre, or on radio or television. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Drama engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-eastern-european-languages-literature-and-culture-bs': "Eastern Europe is a subregion of the European continent. As a largely ambiguous term, it has a wide range of geopolitical, geographical, ethnic, cultural and socio-economic connotations. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Eastern European Languages, Literature, and Culture engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-economics-bs': "Economics is a social science that studies the production, distribution, and consumption of goods and services. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Economics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-english-bs': "English studies is an academic discipline taught in primary, secondary, and post-secondary education in English-speaking countries. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in English engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-ethnomusicology-bs': "Ethnomusicology is the multidisciplinary study of music in its cultural context. The discipline investigates social, cognitive, biological, comparative, and other dimensions. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Ethnomusicology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-finnish-bs': "Finnish is a Finnic language of the Uralic language family, spoken by the majority of the population in Finland and by ethnic Finns outside of Finland. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Finnish engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-french-bs': "French is a Romance language of the Indo-European family. Like all other Romance languages, French and its closest relatives—the langues d'oïl, historically spoken in northern France and southern Belgium—descended from the Vulgar Latin of the Roman Empire. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in French engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-gender-women-and-sexuality-studies-bs': "Women's studies is an academic field that draws on feminist and interdisciplinary methods to place women's lives and experiences at the center of study, while examining social and cultural constructs of gender; systems of privilege and oppression; and the relationships between power and gender as they intersect with ot. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Gender, Women, and Sexuality Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-geography-bs': "Geography is the study of the lands, features, inhabitants, and phenomena of planet Earth. Geography is an all-encompassing discipline that seeks an understanding of Earth and its human and natural complexities—not merely where objects are, but also how they have changed and come to be. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Geography engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-german-studies-bs': "German studies is an academic field that researches, documents and disseminates German language, literature, and culture in its historic and present forms. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in German Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-global-literary-studies-bs': "While most frequently practised with works of different languages, comparative literature may also be performed on works of the same language if the works originate from different nations or cultures in which that language is spoken. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Global Literary Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-greek-bs': "Ancient Greek includes the forms of the Greek language used in ancient Greece and the ancient world from around 1500 BC to 300 BC. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Greek engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-guitar-bs': "The guitar is a stringed musical instrument that is usually fretted and typically has six or twelve strings. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Guitar engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-history-bs': "History is the systematic study of the past, focusing primarily on the human past. As an academic discipline, it analyses and interprets evidence to construct narratives about what happened and explain why it happened. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in History engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-history-and-philosophy-of-science-bs': "The history and philosophy of science (HPS) is an academic discipline that encompasses the history of science and the philosophy of science. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in History and Philosophy of Science engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-individualized-studies-bs': "It draws knowledge from several fields such as sociology, anthropology, psychology, economics, etc. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Individualized Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-industrial-design-bs': "Industrial design is a process of design applied to physical products that are to be manufactured by mass production. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Industrial Design engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-integrated-social-sciences-bs': "Social science is one of the branches of science, devoted to the study of societies and the relationships among members within those societies. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Integrated Social Sciences engages this discipline at the undergraduate level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-interaction-design-bs': 'Interaction design, often abbreviated as IxD, is "the practice of designing interactive digital products, environments, systems, and services." While interaction design has an interest in form, its main area of focus rests on behavior. At the University of Washington\'s College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Interaction Design engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.',
    'uw-international-studies-bs': "International relations is an academic discipline. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in International Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-italian-bs': "Italian is a Romance language of the Indo-European language family. It is a standardised form of literary Florentine Tuscan and, together with Sardinian, is the least differentiated language from Latin. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Italian engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-japanese-bs': "Japanese is the principal language of the Japonic language family spoken by the Japanese people. It has around 123 million speakers, primarily in Japan, the only country where it is the national language, and within the Japanese diaspora worldwide. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Japanese engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-jazz-studies-bs': "Jazz is a music genre that originated in the African-American communities of New Orleans, Louisiana, in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Jazz Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-korean-bs': "Korean is the native language for about 81 million people, mostly of Korean descent. It is the national language of both North Korea and South Korea. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Korean engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-latin-bs': "Latin is a classical language belonging to the Italic branch of the Indo-European languages. Latin was originally spoken by the Latins in Latium, the lower Tiber area around Rome, Italy. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Latin engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-law-societies-and-justice-bs': "The sociology of law, legal sociology, or law and society, is often described as a sub-discipline of sociology or an interdisciplinary approach within legal studies. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Law, Societies, and Justice engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-linguistics-bs': "Linguistics is the scientific study of language. The areas of linguistic analysis are syntax, semantics (meaning), morphology, phonetics, phonology, and pragmatics. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Linguistics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-mathematics-bs': "Mathematics is a field of knowledge concerned with abstract concepts such as numbers, geometric shapes, sets, functions, and probabilities. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Mathematics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-microbiology-bs': "Microbiology is the scientific study of microorganisms, those being of unicellular (single-celled), multicellular, or acellular. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Microbiology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-middle-eastern-languages-and-cultures-bs': "Middle Eastern studies, sometimes referred to as Near Eastern studies, West Asian Studies or South Western Asian studies, is a name given to a number of academic programs associated with the study of the history, culture, politics, economies, and geography of the Middle East, an area that is generally interpreted to co. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Middle Eastern Languages and Cultures engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-music-bs': "Music is the arrangement of sound to create some combination of form, harmony, melody, rhythm, or otherwise expressive content. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Music engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-music-education-bs': "Music education is a field of practice in which educators are trained for careers as elementary or secondary music teachers, school or music conservatory ensemble directors. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Music Education engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-music-theory-bs': "Music theory is the study of theoretical frameworks for understanding the practices and possibilities of music. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Music Theory engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-neuroscience-bs': "Neuroscience is the scientific study of the nervous system, its functions, and its disorders. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Neuroscience engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-norwegian-bs': "Norwegian is a North Germanic language from the Indo-European language family spoken mainly in Norway, where it is an official language. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Norwegian engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-orchestral-instruments-bs': "An orchestra is a large instrumental ensemble typical of classical music or jazz, which combines instruments from different families. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Orchestral Instruments engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-organ-bs': "In music, the organ is a keyboard instrument of one or more pipe divisions or other means for producing tones. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Organ engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-percussion-bs': "A percussion instrument is a musical instrument that is sounded by being struck or scraped by a beater including attached or enclosed beaters or rattles struck, scraped or rubbed by hand or struck against another similar instrument. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Percussion engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-philosophy-bs': "Philosophy is a systematic study of general and fundamental questions concerning topics like existence, knowledge, mind, reason, language, and value. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Philosophy engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-physics-bs': "Physics is the scientific study of matter, its fundamental constituents, its motion and behavior through space and time, and the related entities of energy and force. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Physics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-piano-bs': "A piano is a keyboard instrument that produces sound when its keys are pressed, activating an action mechanism where hammers strike strings. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Piano engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-political-science-bs': "Political science is a field which aims to study the scientific aspect of politics. It deals with systems of governance and power, and the analysis of political activities, political thought, political behavior, and associated constitutions and laws. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Political Science engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-psychology-bs': "Psychology is the scientific study of the mind and behavior. Its subject matter includes the behavior of humans and nonhumans, both conscious and unconscious phenomena, and mental processes such as thoughts, feelings, and motives. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Psychology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-romance-linguistics-bs': "The Romance languages, also known as the Latin or Neo-Latin languages or Latinic languages, are the languages that directly descended from Vulgar Latin. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Romance Linguistics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-russian-language-literature-and-culture-bs': "Russian is an East Slavic language belonging to the Balto-Slavic branch of the Indo-European language family. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Russian Language, Literature, and Culture engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-scandinavian-area-studies-bs': "The Nordic countries are a geographical and cultural region in Northern Europe and North America, as well as the Arctic and North Atlantic oceans. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Scandinavian Area Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-sociology-bs': "Sociology is the scientific study of human society that focuses on society, human social behavior, patterns of social relationships, social interaction, and aspects of culture associated with everyday life. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Sociology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-south-asian-languages-and-cultures-bs': 'Indology is the academic study of Indian history and culture. In modern times Indology has been largely replaced by the term "South Asian studies", which in addition to India, focuses on the region as a whole, and as such is a subset of Asian studies. At the University of Washington\'s College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in South Asian Languages and Cultures engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.',
    'uw-spanish-bs': "Spanish or Castilian is a Romance language of the Indo-European language family that evolved from the Vulgar Latin spoken on the Iberian Peninsula of Europe. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Spanish engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-speech-and-hearing-sciences-bs': "Audiologists treat those with hearing loss and proactively prevent related damage. By employing various testing strategies, audiologists aim to determine whether someone has normal sensitivity to sounds. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Speech and Hearing Sciences engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-statistics-bs': "In applying statistics to a scientific, industrial, or social problem, it is conventional to begin with a statistical population or a statistical model to be studied. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Statistics engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-string-instruments-bs': "In musical instrument classification, string instruments, or chordophones, are musical instruments that produce sound from vibrating strings when a performer strums, plucks, strikes or sounds the strings in varying manners. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in String Instruments engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-swedish-bs': "Swedish is a North Germanic language from the Indo-European language family, spoken predominantly in Sweden and parts of Finland. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Swedish engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-visual-communication-design-bs': "Communication design is a mixed discipline between design and information-development concerned with how media communicates with people. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Visual Communication Design engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-voice-bs': "The human voice consists of sound made by a human being using the vocal tract, including talking, singing, laughing, crying, screaming, shouting, humming or yelling. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Voice engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-anthropology-ms': "Graduate study. Anthropology is the scientific study of humanity that crosses biology and sociology, concerned with human behavior, human biology, cultures, societies, and linguistics, in both the present and past, including archaic humans. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Anthropology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-applied-chemical-science-and-technology-ms': "Chemical engineering is an engineering field which deals with the study of the operation and design of chemical plants as well as methods of improving production. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Applied Chemical Science and Technology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-applied-child-and-adolescent-psychology-prevention-and-treatment-ms': "Developmental psychology is the scientific study of how and why the human mind grows, changes, and adapts over the course of a human lifetime. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Applied Child and Adolescent Psychology: Prevention and Treatment engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-applied-mathematics-ms': "Graduate study. Applied mathematics is the application of mathematical methods by different fields such as physics, engineering, medicine, biology, finance, business, computer science, social science, and industry. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Applied Mathematics engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-art-history-ms': "Graduate study. Art history is an academic discipline devoted to the study of artistic production and visual culture throughout human history. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Art History engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-asian-languages-and-literature-ms': "Graduate study. Asian studies is the term used usually in North America and Australia for what in Europe is known as Oriental studies. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Asian Languages & Literature engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-astronomy-ms': "Graduate study. Astronomy is a natural science that studies celestial objects and the phenomena that occur in the cosmos. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Astronomy engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-chemistry-ms': "Graduate study. Chemistry is the scientific study of the properties and behavior of matter. It is a physical science within the natural sciences that studies matter: composition, structure, properties, behavior and the changes they undergo during reactions with other substances. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Chemistry engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-china-studies-ms': "Sinology, also referred to as China studies, is the academic discipline of studying China, including Chinese culture, Chinese history, and the Chinese language. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in China Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-cinema-and-media-studies-ms': "Graduate study. Film studies is an academic discipline that deals with various theoretical, historical, and critical approaches to cinema as an art form and a medium. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Cinema and Media Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-communication-ms': "Graduate study. Communication is commonly defined as the transmission of information. Its precise definition is disputed and there are disagreements about whether unintentional or failed transmissions are included and whether communication not only transmits meaning but also creates it. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Communication engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-computational-finance-and-risk-management-ms': "Computational finance is a branch of applied computer science that deals with problems of practical interest in finance. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Computational Finance & Risk Management engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-computational-linguistics-ms': "Computational linguistics is an interdisciplinary field concerned with the computational modelling of natural language, as well as the study of appropriate computational approaches to linguistic questions. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Computational Linguistics engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-dance-ms': "Graduate study. Dance is an art form, consisting of sequences of body movements with aesthetic and often symbolic value, either improvised or purposefully selected. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Dance engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-design-ms': "A design is the concept or proposal for an object, process, or system. The word design refers to something that is or has been intentionally created by a thinking agent, and is sometimes used to refer to the inherent nature of something – its design. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Design engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-drama-ms': "Graduate study. Drama is the specific mode of fiction represented in performance: a play, opera, mime, ballet, etc., performed in a theatre, or on radio or television. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Drama engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-east-asia-studies-ms': "East Asian studies is a distinct multidisciplinary field of scholarly enquiry and education that promotes a broad humanistic understanding of East Asia past and present. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in East Asia Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-economics-ms': "Graduate study. Economics is a social science that studies the production, distribution, and consumption of goods and services. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Economics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-english-ms': "Graduate study. English studies is an academic discipline taught in primary, secondary, and post-secondary education in English-speaking countries. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in English engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-feminist-studies-ms': "Graduate study. Feminist Studies is a peer-reviewed academic journal covering women's studies that was established in 1972. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Feminist Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-fine-arts-ms': "In European academic traditions, fine art is considered a kind of high art and is made primarily for aesthetics or creative expression, distinguishing it from popular art, decorative art or applied art, which also either serve some practical function or is generally of limited artistic quality in order to appeal to the. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Fine Arts engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-geography-ms': "Graduate study. Geography is the study of the lands, features, inhabitants, and phenomena of planet Earth. Geography is an all-encompassing discipline that seeks an understanding of Earth and its human and natural complexities—not merely where objects are, but also how they have changed and come to be. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Geography engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-german-studies-ms': "Graduate study. German studies is an academic field that researches, documents and disseminates German language, literature, and culture in its historic and present forms. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in German Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-hispanic-studies-ms': "Graduate study. Hispanism is the study of the literature and culture of the Spanish-speaking world, principally that of Spain and Hispanic America. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Hispanic Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-international-studies-ms': "Graduate study. International relations is an academic discipline. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in International Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-italian-studies-ms': "Italian studies is an interdisciplinary field dealing with the study of the Italian language, literature, art, history, politics, culture and society. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Italian Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-japan-studies-ms': "Japanese studies or Japan studies , sometimes known as Japanology in Europe, is a sub-field of area studies or East Asian studies involved in social sciences and humanities research on Japan. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Japan Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-korea-studies-ms': "Korean studies is an academic discipline that focuses on the study of Korea, which includes South Korea, North Korea, and diasporic Korean populations. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Korea Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-linguistics-ms': "Graduate study. Linguistics is the scientific study of language. The areas of linguistic analysis are syntax, semantics (meaning), morphology, phonetics, phonology, and pragmatics. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Linguistics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-mathematics-ms': "Graduate study. Mathematics is a field of knowledge concerned with abstract concepts such as numbers, geometric shapes, sets, functions, and probabilities. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Mathematics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-music-ms': "Graduate study. Music is the arrangement of sound to create some combination of form, harmony, melody, rhythm, or otherwise expressive content. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Music engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-near-eastern-languages-and-civilization-ms': "The ancient Near East was home to many cradles of civilization, spanning Mesopotamia, the Levant, Egypt, Iran, Anatolia and the Armenian highlands, and the Arabian Peninsula. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Near Eastern Languages & Civilization engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-philosophy-ms': "Graduate study. Philosophy is a systematic study of general and fundamental questions concerning topics like existence, knowledge, mind, reason, language, and value. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Philosophy engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-physics-ms': "Graduate study. Physics is the scientific study of matter, its fundamental constituents, its motion and behavior through space and time, and the related entities of energy and force. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Physics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-political-science-ms': "Graduate study. Political science is a field which aims to study the scientific aspect of politics. It deals with systems of governance and power, and the analysis of political activities, political thought, political behavior, and associated constitutions and laws. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Political Science engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-psychology-ms': "Graduate study. Psychology is the scientific study of the mind and behavior. Its subject matter includes the behavior of humans and nonhumans, both conscious and unconscious phenomena, and mental processes such as thoughts, feelings, and motives. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Psychology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-russia-east-european-and-central-asian-studies-ms': "Area studies, also known as regional studies, is an interdisciplinary field of research and scholarship pertaining to particular geographical, national/federal, or cultural regions. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Russia, East European and Central Asian Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-scandinavian-ms': "Graduate study. The North Germanic languages are one of the three branches of the Germanic languages—a sub-family of the Indo-European languages—along with the West Germanic languages and the extinct East Germanic languages. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Scandinavian engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-slavic-languages-and-literatures-ms': "Graduate study. The Slavic languages, also known as the Slavonic languages, are Indo-European languages spoken primarily by the Slavic peoples and their descendants. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Slavic Languages & Literatures engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-sociology-ms': "Graduate study. Sociology is the scientific study of human society that focuses on society, human social behavior, patterns of social relationships, social interaction, and aspects of culture associated with everyday life. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Sociology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-south-asian-studies-ms': 'In modern times Indology has been largely replaced by the term "South Asian studies", which in addition to India, focuses on the region as a whole, and as such is a subset of Asian studies. At the University of Washington\'s College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in South Asian Studies engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-southeast-asian-studies-ms': "Southeast Asian studies (SEAS) refers to research and education on the language, culture, and history of the different states and ethnic groups of Southeast Asia. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Southeast Asian Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-speech-language-pathology-ms': "Speech–language pathology, also known as speech and language pathology or logopedics, is a healthcare and academic discipline concerning the evaluation, treatment, and prevention of communication disorders, including expressive and mixed receptive-expressive language disorders, voice disorders, speech sound disorders. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Speech-Language Pathology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-statistics-ms': "Graduate study. In applying statistics to a scientific, industrial, or social problem, it is conventional to begin with a statistical population or a statistical model to be studied. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Master of Science in Statistics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-audiology-prof': "Audiology is a branch of science that studies hearing, balance, and related disorders. Audiologists treat those with hearing loss and proactively prevent related damage. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Audiology engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-anthropology-phd': "Doctoral research. Anthropology is the scientific study of humanity that crosses biology and sociology, concerned with human behavior, human biology, cultures, societies, and linguistics, in both the present and past, including archaic humans. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Anthropology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-applied-mathematics-phd': "Doctoral research. Applied mathematics is the application of mathematical methods by different fields such as physics, engineering, medicine, biology, finance, business, computer science, social science, and industry. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Applied Mathematics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-art-history-phd': "Doctoral research. Art history is an academic discipline devoted to the study of artistic production and visual culture throughout human history. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Art History engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-asian-languages-and-literature-phd': "Doctoral research. Asian studies is the term used usually in North America and Australia for what in Europe is known as Oriental studies. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Asian Languages & Literature engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-astronomy-phd': "Doctoral research. Astronomy is a natural science that studies celestial objects and the phenomena that occur in the cosmos. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Astronomy engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-biology-phd': "Doctoral research. Biology is the scientific study of life and living organisms. It is a broad natural science that encompasses a wide range of fields and unifying principles that explain the structure, function, growth, origin, evolution, and distribution of life. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Biology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-chemistry-phd': "Doctoral research. Chemistry is the scientific study of the properties and behavior of matter. It is a physical science within the natural sciences that studies matter: composition, structure, properties, behavior and the changes they undergo during reactions with other substances. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Chemistry engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-cinema-and-media-studies-phd': "Doctoral research. Film studies is an academic discipline that deals with various theoretical, historical, and critical approaches to cinema as an art form and a medium. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Cinema and Media Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-communication-phd': "Doctoral research. Communication is commonly defined as the transmission of information. Its precise definition is disputed and there are disagreements about whether unintentional or failed transmissions are included and whether communication not only transmits meaning but also creates it. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Communication engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-digital-arts-and-experimental-media-phd': "Digital art, or the digital arts, is artistic work that uses digital technology as part of the creative or presentational process. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Digital Arts & Experimental Media engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-drama-phd': "Doctoral research. Drama is the specific mode of fiction represented in performance: a play, opera, mime, ballet, etc., performed in a theatre, or on radio or television. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Drama engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-economics-phd': "Doctoral research. Economics is a social science that studies the production, distribution, and consumption of goods and services. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Economics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-english-phd': "Doctoral research. English studies is an academic discipline taught in primary, secondary, and post-secondary education in English-speaking countries. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in English engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-feminist-studies-phd': "Doctoral research. Feminist Studies is a peer-reviewed academic journal covering women's studies that was established in 1972. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Feminist Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-french-studies-phd': "French Studies is a quarterly peer-reviewed academic journal published by Oxford University Press on behalf of the Society for French Studies. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in French Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-geography-phd': "Doctoral research. Geography is the study of the lands, features, inhabitants, and phenomena of planet Earth. Geography is an all-encompassing discipline that seeks an understanding of Earth and its human and natural complexities—not merely where objects are, but also how they have changed and come to be. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Geography engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-german-studies-phd': "Doctoral research. German studies is an academic field that researches, documents and disseminates German language, literature, and culture in its historic and present forms. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in German Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-hispanic-studies-phd': "Doctoral research. Hispanism is the study of the literature and culture of the Spanish-speaking world, principally that of Spain and Hispanic America. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Hispanic Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-history-phd': "Doctoral research. History is the systematic study of the past, focusing primarily on the human past. As an academic discipline, it analyses and interprets evidence to construct narratives about what happened and explain why it happened. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in History engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-linguistics-phd': "Doctoral research. Linguistics is the scientific study of language. The areas of linguistic analysis are syntax, semantics (meaning), morphology, phonetics, phonology, and pragmatics. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Linguistics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-mathematics-phd': "Doctoral research. Mathematics is a field of knowledge concerned with abstract concepts such as numbers, geometric shapes, sets, functions, and probabilities. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Mathematics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-music-phd': "Doctoral research. Music is the arrangement of sound to create some combination of form, harmony, melody, rhythm, or otherwise expressive content. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Music engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-musical-arts-phd': "Music is generally agreed to be a cultural universal that is present in all human societies. Definitions of music vary widely in substance and approach. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Musical Arts engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-near-and-middle-eastern-studies-phd': "It is considered a form of area studies, taking an overtly interdisciplinary approach to the study of a region. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Near & Middle Eastern Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-philosophy-phd': "Doctoral research. Philosophy is a systematic study of general and fundamental questions concerning topics like existence, knowledge, mind, reason, language, and value. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Philosophy engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-physics-phd': "Doctoral research. Physics is the scientific study of matter, its fundamental constituents, its motion and behavior through space and time, and the related entities of energy and force. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Physics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-political-science-phd': "Doctoral research. Political science is a field which aims to study the scientific aspect of politics. It deals with systems of governance and power, and the analysis of political activities, political thought, political behavior, and associated constitutions and laws. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Political Science engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-psychology-phd': "Doctoral research. Psychology is the scientific study of the mind and behavior. Its subject matter includes the behavior of humans and nonhumans, both conscious and unconscious phenomena, and mental processes such as thoughts, feelings, and motives. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Psychology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-scandinavian-phd': "Doctoral research. The North Germanic languages are one of the three branches of the Germanic languages—a sub-family of the Indo-European languages—along with the West Germanic languages and the extinct East Germanic languages. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Scandinavian engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-slavic-languages-and-literatures-phd': "Doctoral research. The Slavic languages, also known as the Slavonic languages, are Indo-European languages spoken primarily by the Slavic peoples and their descendants. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Slavic Languages & Literatures engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-sociology-phd': "Doctoral research. Sociology is the scientific study of human society that focuses on society, human social behavior, patterns of social relationships, social interaction, and aspects of culture associated with everyday life. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Sociology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-speech-and-hearing-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Audiologists treat those with hearing loss and proactively prevent related damage. By employing various testing strategies, audiologists aim to determine whether someone has normal sensitivity to sounds. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Speech and Hearing Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-statistics-phd': "Doctoral research. In applying statistics to a scientific, industrial, or social problem, it is conventional to begin with a statistical population or a statistical model to be studied. At the University of Washington's College of Arts and Sciences in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Statistics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-architectural-design-bs': "Architectural Design, also known as AD, is a New York-based architectural publication first launched in the UK, in 1930, as Architectural Design and Construction. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Architectural Design engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-architectural-design-w-const-mgmt-bs': "Architectural design values make up an important part of what influences architects and designers when they make their design decisions. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Architectural Design (w/Const Mgmt) engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-architectural-studies-bs': "Architecture is the study and practice of designing structures, especially habitable ones. It utilizes civil engineering techniques, but is considered a visual art. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Architectural Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-community-environment-and-planning-bs': "Urban planning is the process of developing and designing plans for land use and the built environment, including air, water, and the infrastructure passing into and out of urban areas, such as transportation, communications, and distribution networks, and their accessibility. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Community, Environment, and Planning engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-environmental-design-and-sustainability-bs': "Environmental design is the process of addressing surrounding environmental parameters when devising plans, programs, policies, buildings, or products. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Environmental Design and Sustainability engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-real-estate-bs': "Real estate is a property consisting of land and the buildings on it, along with its natural resources such as growing crops, minerals or water, and wild animals, immovable property of this nature, real property or housing in general. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Real Estate engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-architecture-ms': "It utilizes civil engineering techniques, but is considered a visual art. It is both the process and the product of sketching, conceiving, planning, designing, and constructing buildings or other structures. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Architecture engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-concurrent-ms': "Concurrent computing is a form of computing in which several computations are executed concurrently—during overlapping time periods—instead of sequentially—with one completing before the next starts. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Concurrent engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-construction-management-ms': "Construction management (CM) is a professional service that applies project management techniques to the planning, design, and construction of a project, from its beginning to its completion. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Construction Management engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-infrastructure-planning-and-management-ms': "Graduate study. Infrastructure is the set of facilities and systems that serve a country, city, or other area, and encompasses the services and facilities necessary for its economy, households and firms to function. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Infrastructure Planning & Management engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-infrastructure-planning-and-management-ms-2': "Graduate study. Infrastructure is composed of public and private physical structures such as roads, railways, bridges, airports, public transit systems, tunnels, water supply, sewers, electrical grids, and telecommunications. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Infrastructure Planning & Management (Online) engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-landscape-architecture-ms': "Landscape architecture is the design of outdoor areas, landmarks, and structures to achieve environmental, social-behavioural, or aesthetic outcomes. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Landscape Architecture engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-real-estate-ms': "Graduate study. Real estate is a property consisting of land and the buildings on it, along with its natural resources such as growing crops, minerals or water, and wild animals, immovable property of this nature, real property or housing in general. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Real Estate engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-urban-planning-ms': "The primary concern was the public welfare, which included considerations of efficiency, sanitation, protection and use of the environment, as well as taking account of effects of the master plans on the social and economic activities. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Master of Science in Urban Planning engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-built-environment-phd': "The term built environment refers to human-made conditions and is often used in architecture, landscape architecture, urban planning, public health, sociology, and anthropology, among others. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Built Environment engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-urban-design-and-planning-phd': "Traditionally, urban planning followed a top-down approach in master planning the physical layout of human settlements. At the University of Washington's College of Built Environments in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Urban Design & Planning engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-accounting-bs': "Accounting, also known as accountancy, is the process of recording and processing information about economic entities, such as businesses and corporations. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Accounting engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-accounting-for-business-professionals-bs': "Accounting measures the results of an organization's economic activities and conveys this information to a variety of stakeholders, including investors, creditors, management, and regulators. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Accounting for Business Professionals engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-entrepreneurship-bs': "Entrepreneurship is the creation or extraction of economic value by identifying and commercializing opportunities to deliver products or services, a process that typically requires considerable initiation and bears risk. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Entrepreneurship engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-finance-bs': "Finance refers to resources and the discipline that studies such resources, allowing an entity to gain the consumption and saving opportunity within a specified timeframe, with related concepts such as income, money, currency, assets and liabilities. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Finance engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-human-resources-management-bs': "Human resource management (HRM) is the strategic and coherent approach to the effective and efficient management of people in a company or organization. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Human Resources Management engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-information-systems-bs': "An information system (IS) is a formal, sociotechnical, and organizational system designed to collect, process, store, and distribute information. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Information Systems engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-marketing-bs': "Marketing is the act of acquiring, satisfying and retaining customers. It is one of the primary components of business management and commerce. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Marketing engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-operations-and-supply-chain-management-bs': "In commerce, supply chain management (SCM) deals with a system of procurement, operations management, logistics and marketing channels, through which raw materials can be developed into finished products and delivered to their end customers. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Operations and Supply Chain Management engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-business-administration-ms': "Graduate study. Business administration, also known as business management is the administration of a commercial enterprise. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Business Administration engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-business-analytics-ms': "Business analytics (BA) refers to the skills, technologies, and practices for iterative exploration and investigation of past business performance to gain insight and drive business planning. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Business Analytics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-entrepreneurship-ms': "Graduate study. Entrepreneurship is the creation or extraction of economic value by identifying and commercializing opportunities to deliver products or services, a process that typically requires considerable initiation and bears risk. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Entrepreneurship engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-information-systems-ms': "Graduate study. An information system (IS) is a formal, sociotechnical, and organizational system designed to collect, process, store, and distribute information. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Information Systems engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-professional-accounting-ms': 'Practitioners of accounting are known as accountants. The terms "accounting" and "financial reporting" are often used interchangeably. At the University of Washington\'s Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Professional Accounting engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-supply-chain-management-ms': 'A more narrow definition of supply chain management is the "design, planning, execution, control, and monitoring of supply chain activities with the objective of creating net value, building a competitive infrastructure, leveraging worldwide logistics, synchronising supply with demand and measuring performance globally. At the University of Washington\'s Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Supply Chain Management engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-taxation-ms': "A tax is a mandatory financial charge or levy imposed on an individual or legal entity by a governmental organization to support government spending and public expenditures collectively or to regulate economic activity through measures designed to mitigate negative externalities. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Master of Science in Taxation engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-business-administration-phd': "Doctoral research. Business administration, also known as business management is the administration of a commercial enterprise. At the University of Washington's Michael G. Foster School of Business in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Business Administration engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-dentistry-ms': "Graduate study. Dentistry, also known as dental medicine and oral medicine, is the branch of medicine focused on the teeth, gums, and mouth. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Dentistry engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-endodontics-ms': "Endodontics is the dental specialty concerned with the study and treatment of the dental pulp. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Endodontics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-oral-health-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. It consists of the study, diagnosis, prevention, management, and treatment of diseases, disorders, and conditions of the mouth, most commonly focused on dentition as well as the oral mucosa. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Oral Health Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-oral-medicine-ms': "An oral medicine or stomatology doctor/dentist has received additional specialized training and experience in the diagnosis and management of oral mucosal abnormalities including oral cancer, salivary gland disorders, temporomandibular disorders and facial pain, taste and smell disorders; and recognition of the oral ma. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Oral Medicine engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-orthodontics-ms': "Orthodontics is a dentistry specialty that addresses the diagnosis, prevention, management, and correction of mal-positioned teeth and jaws, as well as misaligned bite patterns. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Orthodontics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-periodontics-ms': "Periodontology or periodontics is the specialty of dentistry that studies supporting structures of teeth, as well as diseases and conditions that affect them. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Periodontics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-prosthodontics-ms': "Prosthodontics, also known as dental prosthetics or prosthetic dentistry, is the area of dentistry that focuses on dental prostheses. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Master of Science in Prosthodontics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-dentistry-prof': "Professional study. Dentistry, also known as dental medicine and oral medicine, is the branch of medicine focused on the teeth, gums, and mouth. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Doctor of Dental Surgery engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-dentistry-phd': "Doctoral research. Dentistry, also known as dental medicine and oral medicine, is the branch of medicine focused on the teeth, gums, and mouth. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Dentistry engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-oral-health-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. It consists of the study, diagnosis, prevention, management, and treatment of diseases, disorders, and conditions of the mouth, most commonly focused on dentition as well as the oral mucosa. At the University of Washington's School of Dentistry in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Oral Health Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-early-care-and-education-bs': "Early childhood education (ECE) is a branch of education theory that relates to the teaching of children from birth up to the age of eight. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Early Care and Education engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-early-care-and-education-fee-based-online-bs': "Traditionally, this is up to the equivalent of third grade. ECE is described as an important period in child development. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Early Care and Education (fee-based) (online) engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-early-childhood-and-family-studies-bs': "ECE is described as an important period in child development. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Early Childhood and Family Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-education-studies-bs': "Pedagogy, most commonly understood as the approach to teaching, is the theory and practice of learning, and how this process influences, and is influenced by, the social, political, and psychological development of learners. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Education Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-education-communities-and-organizations-bs': "Education is the transmission of knowledge and skills and the development of character traits. Formal education happens in a complex institutional framework, like public schools. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Education, Communities and Organizations engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-curriculum-and-instruction-ms': "Graduate study. Curriculum and Instruction is a field within education which seeks to research, develop, and implement curriculum changes that increase learner achievement in educational settings. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Curriculum & Instruction engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-educational-foundations-leadership-and-policy-ms': "Education governance is often shared across local, state, and federal levels. Some analysts view education policy as a form of social engineering. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Educational Foundations, Leadership & Policy engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-educational-leadership-and-policy-studies-ms': "Graduate study. Educational leadership is the process of enlisting and guiding the talents and energies of teachers, students, and parents toward achieving common educational aims. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Educational Leadership & Policy Studies engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-learning-sciences-and-human-development-ms': "LS research traditionally focuses on cognitive-psychological, sociocultural, and critical theoretical foundations of human learning, as well as practical design of learning environments. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Learning Sciences & Human Development engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-master-in-teaching-ms': "Teacher education or teacher training refers to programs, policies, procedures, and provision designed to equip (prospective) teachers with the knowledge, attitudes, behaviors, approaches, methodologies and skills they require to perform their tasks effectively in the classroom, school, and wider community. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Master In Teaching engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-measurement-and-statistics-ms': "Statistics is the discipline that concerns the collection, organization, analysis, interpretation, and presentation of data. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Measurement & Statistics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-special-education-ms': "Graduate study. This involves the individually planned and systematically monitored arrangement of teaching procedures, adapted equipment and materials, and accessible settings. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Master of Science in Special Education engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-curriculum-and-instruction-phd': "Doctoral research. Curriculum and Instruction is a field within education which seeks to research, develop, and implement curriculum changes that increase learner achievement in educational settings. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Curriculum & Instruction engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-curriculum-and-instruction-phd': "In education, a curriculum is the totality of student experiences that occur in an educational process. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: Curriculum & Instruction engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-educ-leadershp-and-policy-st-phd': "Education policy consists of the principles and policy decisions that influence the field of education, as well as the collection of laws and rules that govern the operation of education systems. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: Educ Leadershp & Policy St engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-learning-sciences-and-human-development-phd': "Learning sciences (LS) is an interdisciplinary field of study dedicated to the empirical investigation of learning, exploration of what might be important for people to learn and why, engagement in the design and implementation of learning innovations, and the improvement of instructional methodologies. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: Learning Sciences & Human Development engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-measurement-and-statistics-phd': "Educational measurement refers to the use of educational assessments and the analysis of data such as scores obtained from educational assessments to infer the abilities and proficiencies of students. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: Measurement & Statistics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-school-psychology-phd': "School psychology is a field that applies principles from educational psychology, developmental psychology, community psychology, and behavior analysis to meet the learning and behavioral health needs of children and adolescents. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: School Psychology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-education-special-education-phd': "Special education, also called SPED, special ed, aided education, alternative provision, exceptional student education, or special day class (SDC), is the practice of educating students in a way that accommodates their individual differences, disabilities, and special needs. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Education: Special Education engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-educational-leadership-and-policy-studies-phd': "Doctoral research. Educational leadership is the process of enlisting and guiding the talents and energies of teachers, students, and parents toward achieving common educational aims. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Educational Leadership & Policy Studies engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-special-education-phd': "Doctoral research. This involves the individually planned and systematically monitored arrangement of teaching procedures, adapted equipment and materials, and accessible settings. At the University of Washington's College of Education in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Special Education engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-engineering-bs': "Engineering is the practice of systematically applying natural science and mathematics to design and improve systems, devices, or processes that solve problems under constraints. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Engineering engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-aeronautics-and-astronautics-ms': "It has two major and overlapping branches: aeronautical engineering and astronautical engineering. Avionics engineering is similar, but deals with the electronics side of aerospace engineering. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Aeronautics and Astronautics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-aerospace-engineering-ms': "Avionics engineering is similar, but deals with the electronics side of aerospace engineering. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Aerospace Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-applied-bioengineering-ms': "Biomedical engineering (BME) or medical engineering is the application of engineering principles and design concepts to medicine and biology for healthcare applications. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Applied Bioengineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-artificial-intelligence-and-machine-learning-for-engineering-ms': "Machine learning (ML) is a field of study in artificial intelligence concerned with the development and study of statistical algorithms that can learn from data and generalize to unseen data, and thus perform tasks without being explicitly programmed. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning for Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-bioengineering-ms': "Graduate study. Biological engineering or bioengineering is the application of principles of biology and the tools of engineering to create usable, tangible, economically viable products. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Bioengineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-chemical-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Chemical engineers develop economical commercial processes to convert raw materials into useful products. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Chemical Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-civil-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Civil engineering is a professional engineering discipline that deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and naturally built environment, including public works such as roads, bridges, canals, dams, airports, sewage systems, pipelines, structural components of buildings, and railways. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Civil Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-computer-science-and-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Computer science and engineering (CSE) is an academic subject comprising approaches of computer science and computer engineering. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Computer Science & Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-electrical-and-computer-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Electrical engineering is an engineering discipline concerned with the study, design, and application of equipment, devices, and systems that use electricity, electronics, and electromagnetism. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Electrical and Computer Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-engineering-in-leadership-and-systems-innovation-ms': "Systems engineering is an interdisciplinary field of engineering and engineering management that focuses on how to design, integrate, and manage complex systems over their life cycles. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Engineering in Leadership and Systems Innovation engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-engineering-in-multidisciplinary-engineering-ms': "It is typically motivated by satisfying human needs, resulting in creations such as bridges, engines, smartphones, pacemakers, the internet, spacecraft, and washing machines. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Engineering in Multidisciplinary Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-human-centered-design-and-engineering-ms': "Human-centered design, as used in ISO standards, is an approach to problem-solving commonly used in process, product, service and system design, management, and engineering frameworks that develops solutions to problems by involving the human perspective in all steps of the problem-solving process. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Human Centered Design & Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-industrial-and-systems-engineering-ms': "Industrial engineering (IE) is concerned with the design, improvement and installation of integrated systems of people, materials, information, equipment and energy. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Industrial & Systems Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-industrial-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. It draws upon specialized knowledge and skill in the mathematical, physical, and social sciences together with the principles and methods of engineering analysis and design, to specify, predict, and evaluate the results to be obtained from such systems. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Industrial Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-materials-science-and-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Materials science is an interdisciplinary field concerned with understanding the relationships between the structure of materials and their properties and using this knowledge to design materials for specific applications. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Materials Science & Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-materials-science-and-engineering-ms-2': "The internal structure of a material—from atomic arrangements to microscopic features—strongly influences its mechanical, electrical, thermal, and optical behavior. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Materials Science and Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-mechanical-engineering-ms': 'Graduate study. The American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) is an American professional association that, in its own words, "promotes the art, science, and practice of multidisciplinary engineering and allied sciences around the globe" via "continuing education, training and professional development, codes and standards, resea. At the University of Washington\'s College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering engages this discipline at the master\'s level. The program is offered fully online.',
    'uw-pharmaceutical-bioengineering-ms': "Pharmaceutical engineering is a branch of engineering focused on discovering, formulating, and manufacturing medication, analytical and quality control processes, and on designing, building, and improving manufacturing sites that produce drugs. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Pharmaceutical Bioengineering engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-supply-chain-transportation-and-logistics-ms': "Logistics is the part of supply chain management that deals with the efficient forward and reverse flow of goods, services, and related information from the point of origin to the point of consumption according to the needs of customers, and a logistician is a professional working in the field of logistics management. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Supply Chain Transportation & Logistics engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-sustainable-transportation-ms': "Sustainable transport is transportation sustainable in terms of its social and environmental impacts. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Sustainable Transportation engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-technology-innovation-ms': "Innovation is the practical implementation of ideas that result in the creation or improvements of goods or services. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Master of Science in Technology Innovation engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-aeronautics-and-astronautics-phd': "Aerospace engineering is the primary field of engineering concerned with the development of aircraft and spacecraft. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Aeronautics & Astronautics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-bioengineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Biological engineering or bioengineering is the application of principles of biology and the tools of engineering to create usable, tangible, economically viable products. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Bioengineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-chemical-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Chemical engineers develop economical commercial processes to convert raw materials into useful products. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Chemical Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-civil-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Civil engineering is a professional engineering discipline that deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and naturally built environment, including public works such as roads, bridges, canals, dams, airports, sewage systems, pipelines, structural components of buildings, and railways. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Civil Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-computer-science-and-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Computer science and engineering (CSE) is an academic subject comprising approaches of computer science and computer engineering. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Computer Science & Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-electrical-and-computer-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Electrical engineering is an engineering discipline concerned with the study, design, and application of equipment, devices, and systems that use electricity, electronics, and electromagnetism. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Electrical and Computer Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-industrial-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. It draws upon specialized knowledge and skill in the mathematical, physical, and social sciences together with the principles and methods of engineering analysis and design, to specify, predict, and evaluate the results to be obtained from such systems. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Industrial Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-materials-science-and-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Materials science is an interdisciplinary field concerned with understanding the relationships between the structure of materials and their properties and using this knowledge to design materials for specific applications. At the University of Washington's College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Materials Science & Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-mechanical-engineering-phd': 'Doctoral research. The American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) is an American professional association that, in its own words, "promotes the art, science, and practice of multidisciplinary engineering and allied sciences around the globe" via "continuing education, training and professional development, codes and standards, resea. At the University of Washington\'s College of Engineering in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Mechanical Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.',
    'uw-aquatic-conservation-and-ecology-bs': "An aquatic ecosystem is an ecosystem found in and around a body of water, in contrast to land-based terrestrial ecosystems. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Aquatic Conservation and Ecology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-atmospheric-and-climate-science-bs': "Atmospheric science is the study of the Earth's atmosphere and its various inner-working physical processes. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Atmospheric and Climate Science engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-earth-and-space-sciences-bs': "This is a branch of science dealing with the physical, chemical, and biological complex constitutions and synergistic linkages of Earth's four spheres: the biosphere, hydrosphere/cryosphere, atmosphere, and geosphere. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Earth and Space Sciences engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-environmental-science-and-terrestrial-resource-management-bs': "Environmental science is an academic field that integrates the physical, biological, and mathematical sciences to study the environment and solve environmental problems. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Environmental Science and Terrestrial Resource Management engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-environmental-studies-bs': "Environmental studies is a multidisciplinary academic field which systematically studies human interaction with the environment. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Environmental Studies engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-marine-biology-bs': "Marine biology is the scientific study of the biology of marine life, organisms that inhabit the sea. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Marine Biology engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-oceanography-bs': "Oceanography, also known as oceanology, sea science, ocean science, and marine science, is the scientific study of the ocean, including its physics, chemistry, biology, and geology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Oceanography engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-sustainable-bioresource-systems-engineering-bs': "Biological systems engineering or biosystems engineering is a broad-based engineering discipline with particular emphasis on non-medical biology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Sustainable Bioresource Systems Engineering engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-aquatic-and-fishery-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. Fisheries science is the academic discipline of managing and understanding fisheries. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Aquatic & Fishery Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-atmospheric-and-climate-science-ms': "Graduate study. Atmospheric science is the study of the Earth's atmosphere and its various inner-working physical processes. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Atmospheric and Climate Science engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-earth-and-space-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. Earth science or geoscience includes all fields of natural science related to planet Earth. This is a branch of science dealing with the physical, chemical, and biological complex constitutions and synergistic linkages of Earth's four spheres: the biosphere, hydrosphere/cryosphere, atmosphere, and geosphere. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Earth & Space Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-environmental-and-forest-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. Forestry is the science and craft of creating, managing, planting, using, conserving and repairing forests and woodlands for associated resources for human and environmental benefits. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Environmental & Forest Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-forest-resources-ms': "Forestry is practiced in plantations and natural stands. The science of forestry has elements that belong to the biological, physical, social, political and managerial sciences. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Forest Resources engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-marine-affairs-ms': "Ocean governance is the conduct of the policy, actions and affairs regarding the world's oceans. Within governance, it incorporates the influence of non-state actors, i.e. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Marine Affairs engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-oceanography-ms': "Graduate study. Oceanography, also known as oceanology, sea science, ocean science, and marine science, is the scientific study of the ocean, including its physics, chemistry, biology, and geology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Oceanography engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-quantitative-ecology-and-resource-management-ms': "Graduate study. Quantitative ecology is the application of advanced mathematical and statistical tools to any number of problems in the field of ecology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Master of Science in Quantitative Ecology & Resource Management engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-aquatic-and-fishery-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Fisheries science is the academic discipline of managing and understanding fisheries. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Aquatic & Fishery Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-atmospheric-and-climate-science-phd': "Doctoral research. Atmospheric science is the study of the Earth's atmosphere and its various inner-working physical processes. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Atmospheric and Climate Science engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-earth-and-space-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Earth science or geoscience includes all fields of natural science related to planet Earth. This is a branch of science dealing with the physical, chemical, and biological complex constitutions and synergistic linkages of Earth's four spheres: the biosphere, hydrosphere/cryosphere, atmosphere, and geosphere. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Earth & Space Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-environmental-and-forest-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Forestry is the science and craft of creating, managing, planting, using, conserving and repairing forests and woodlands for associated resources for human and environmental benefits. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Environmental & Forest Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-oceanography-phd': "Doctoral research. Oceanography, also known as oceanology, sea science, ocean science, and marine science, is the scientific study of the ocean, including its physics, chemistry, biology, and geology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Oceanography engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-quantitative-ecology-and-resource-management-phd': "Doctoral research. Quantitative ecology is the application of advanced mathematical and statistical tools to any number of problems in the field of ecology. At the University of Washington's College of the Environment in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Quantitative Ecology & Resource Management engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-information-management-ms': "Information management (IM) is the appropriate and optimized capture, storage, retrieval, and use of information. At the University of Washington's The Information School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Information Management engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-information-science-ms': "Graduate study. Information science is an academic field that is primarily concerned with the analysis, collection, classification, manipulation, storage, retrieval, movement, dissemination, and protection of information. At the University of Washington's The Information School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Information Science engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-library-and-information-science-ms': "Library and Information Science (LIS) are two academic disciplines that study all aspects of the creation, organization, documentation, management, communication, and use of recorded information. At the University of Washington's The Information School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Library & Information Science engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-museology-ms': "Museology is the study of museums. It explores the history of museums and their role in society, as well as the activities they engage in, including curating, preservation, public programming, and education. At the University of Washington's The Information School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Museology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-information-science-phd': "Doctoral research. Information science is an academic field that is primarily concerned with the analysis, collection, classification, manipulation, storage, retrieval, movement, dissemination, and protection of information. At the University of Washington's The Information School in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Information Science engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-data-science-ms': "Data science is an interdisciplinary academic field that uses statistics, scientific computing, scientific methods, processing, scientific visualization, algorithms, coding, and systems to extract or extrapolate knowledge from potentially noisy, structured, or unstructured data. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Data Science engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-human-computer-interaction-and-design-ms': "Human–computer interaction (HCI) is the process through which people operate and engage with computer systems. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Human-Computer Interaction & Design engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-molecular-and-cellular-biology-ms': "Graduate study. Molecular and Cellular Biology is a biweekly peer-reviewed scientific journal covering all aspects of molecular and cellular biology. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Molecular & Cellular Biology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-molecular-engineering-ms': "Graduate study. Molecular engineering is an emerging field of study concerned with the design and testing of molecular properties, behavior and interactions in order to assemble better materials, systems, and processes for specific functions. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Molecular Engineering engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-neuroscience-ms': "Graduate study. Neuroscience is the scientific study of the nervous system, its functions, and its disorders. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Master of Science in Neuroscience engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-individual-phd-phd': "Interdisciplinarity, also known as interdisciplinary studies, is the combination of multiple academic disciplines into one activity. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Individual PhD engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-molecular-and-cellular-biology-phd': "Doctoral research. Molecular and Cellular Biology is a biweekly peer-reviewed scientific journal covering all aspects of molecular and cellular biology. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Molecular & Cellular Biology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-molecular-engineering-phd': "Doctoral research. Molecular engineering is an emerging field of study concerned with the design and testing of molecular properties, behavior and interactions in order to assemble better materials, systems, and processes for specific functions. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Molecular Engineering engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-neuroscience-phd': "Doctoral research. Neuroscience is the scientific study of the nervous system, its functions, and its disorders. At the University of Washington's The Graduate School in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Neuroscience engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-jurisprudence-ms': "Jurisprudence, also known as theory of law or philosophy of law, is the examination, in a general perspective of what law is and what it ought to be. At the University of Washington's School of Law in Seattle, the Master of Science in Jurisprudence engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-laws-ms': "It has been variously described as a science and as the art of justice. State-enforced laws can be made by a legislature, resulting in statutes; by the executive through decrees and regulations; or by judges' decisions, which form precedent in common law jurisdictions. At the University of Washington's School of Law in Seattle, the Master of Science in Laws engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-laws-in-taxation-ms': "Tax law or revenue law is an area of legal study in which public or sanctioned authorities, such as federal, state and municipal governments use a body of rules and procedures (laws) to assess and collect taxes in a legal context. At the University of Washington's School of Law in Seattle, the Master of Science in Laws In Taxation engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-law-prof': "Professional study. Law is a set of rules that are created and enforced by governmental or societal institutions to regulate behavior, with its precise definition a matter of longstanding debate. At the University of Washington's School of Law in Seattle, the Juris Doctor engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-law-phd': "Doctoral research. Law is a set of rules that are created and enforced by governmental or societal institutions to regulate behavior, with its precise definition a matter of longstanding debate. At the University of Washington's School of Law in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Law engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-anatomic-pathology-ms': "Anatomical pathology (Commonwealth) or anatomic pathology (U.S.) is a medical specialty that is concerned with the diagnosis of disease based on the macroscopic, microscopic, biochemical, immunologic and molecular examination of organs and tissues. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Anatomic Pathology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-biochemistry-ms': "Graduate study. Biochemistry, or biological chemistry, is the study of chemical processes within and relating to living organisms. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Biochemistry engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-bioethics-ms': "Bioethics is both a field of study and professional practice, interested in ethical issues related to health, including those emerging from advances in biology, medicine, and technologies. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Bioethics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-biomedical-and-health-informatics-ms': "Graduate study. Health informatics is the study and implementation of computer science to improve communication, understanding, and management of medical information. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Biomedical & Health Informatics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-clinical-health-services-ms': "Health services research (HSR) became a burgeoning field in North America in the 1960s, when scientific information and policy deliberation began to coalesce. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Clinical Health Services engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-comparative-medicine-ms': "Veterinary medicine is the branch of medicine concerned with the prevention, management, diagnosis, and treatment of disease, disorder, and injury in non-human animals. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Comparative Medicine engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-genetic-counseling-ms': "Genetic counseling is the process of investigating individuals and families affected by or at risk of genetic disorders to help them understand and adapt to the medical, psychological and familial implications of genetic contributions to disease. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Genetic Counseling engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-genome-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. Genomics is an interdisciplinary field of molecular biology focusing on the structure, function, evolution, mapping, and editing of genomes. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Genome Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-health-metrics-sciences-ms': "Health indicators are quantifiable characteristics of a population which researchers use as supporting evidence for describing the health of a population. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Health Metrics Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-immunology-ms': "Graduate study. Immunology is a branch of biology and medicine that covers the study of immune systems in all organisms. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Immunology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-laboratory-medicine-ms': "A medical laboratory or clinical laboratory is a laboratory where tests are conducted out on clinical specimens to obtain information about the health of a patient to aid in diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of disease. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Laboratory Medicine engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-microbiology-ms': "Graduate study. Microbiology is the scientific study of microorganisms, those being of unicellular (single-celled), multicellular, or acellular. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Microbiology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-molecular-medicine-and-mechanisms-of-disease-ms': "Graduate study. Molecular medicine is a broad field, where physical, chemical, biological, bioinformatics and medical techniques are used to describe molecular structures and mechanisms, identify fundamental molecular and genetic errors of disease, and to develop molecular interventions to correct them. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Molecular Medicine and Mechanisms of Disease engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-neurobiology-and-biophysics-ms': "Graduate study. Biophysics is an interdisciplinary science that applies approaches and methods traditionally used in physics to study biological phenomena. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Neurobiology and Biophysics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-occupational-therapy-ms': "Occupational therapy (OT), also known as ergotherapy in Europe, is a healthcare profession that helps people take part in the everyday activities, or occupations, that are important for daily life. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Occupational Therapy engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-pharmacology-ms': "Graduate study. Pharmacology is the science of drugs and medications, including a substance's origin, composition and interaction with biological systems; specifically through pharmacokinetics, pharmacodynamics, therapeutic use, and toxicology. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Pharmacology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-prosthetics-and-orthotics-ms': "In medicine, a prosthesis, or a prosthetic implant, is an artificial device that replaces a missing body part, which may be lost through physical trauma, disease, or a condition present at birth. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Prosthetics & Orthotics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-rehabilitation-medicine-ms': "Physical medicine and rehabilitation (PM&R), also known as physiatry, and outside the United States as physical and rehabilitation medicine (PRM), is a branch of medicine that aims to enhance and restore functional ability and quality of life to people with physical impairments or disabilities. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Master of Science in Rehabilitation Medicine engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-medicine-prof': "Medicine is the science and practice of caring for patients, managing the diagnosis, prognosis, prevention, treatment and palliation of their injury or disease, while promoting their health. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Medicine engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-physical-therapy-prof': "Physical therapy (PT), also known as physiotherapy, is a healthcare profession, as well as the care provided by physical therapists. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Physical Therapy engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-biochemistry-phd': "Doctoral research. Biochemistry, or biological chemistry, is the study of chemical processes within and relating to living organisms. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Biochemistry engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-biomedical-and-health-informatics-phd': "Doctoral research. Health informatics is the study and implementation of computer science to improve communication, understanding, and management of medical information. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Biomedical & Health Informatics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-genome-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Genomics is an interdisciplinary field of molecular biology focusing on the structure, function, evolution, mapping, and editing of genomes. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Genome Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-health-metrics-global-health-metrics-and-implementation-sciences-phd': "It aims to understand the most effective pathways from research to practical application, particularly in areas such as health, education, psychology and management. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Health Metrics: Global Health Metrics & Implementation Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-immunology-phd': "Doctoral research. Immunology is a branch of biology and medicine that covers the study of immune systems in all organisms. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Immunology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-microbiology-phd': "Doctoral research. Microbiology is the scientific study of microorganisms, those being of unicellular (single-celled), multicellular, or acellular. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Microbiology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-molecular-medicine-and-mechanisms-of-disease-phd': "Doctoral research. Molecular medicine is a broad field, where physical, chemical, biological, bioinformatics and medical techniques are used to describe molecular structures and mechanisms, identify fundamental molecular and genetic errors of disease, and to develop molecular interventions to correct them. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Molecular Medicine and Mechanisms of Disease engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-neurobiology-and-biophysics-phd': "Doctoral research. Biophysics is an interdisciplinary science that applies approaches and methods traditionally used in physics to study biological phenomena. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Neurobiology and Biophysics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-pharmacology-phd': "Doctoral research. Pharmacology is the science of drugs and medications, including a substance's origin, composition and interaction with biological systems; specifically through pharmacokinetics, pharmacodynamics, therapeutic use, and toxicology. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Pharmacology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-rehabilitation-science-phd': "Science Publishing Group (SPG), also known as SciencePG, is a predatory publisher of open-access academic journals and books established in 2012. At the University of Washington's School of Medicine in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Rehabilitation Science engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-nursing-ms': 'Graduate study. Nursing is a health care profession that "integrates the art and science of caring and focuses on the protection, promotion, and optimization of health and human functioning; prevention of illness and injury; facilitation of healing; and alleviation of suffering through compassionate presence". At the University of Washington\'s School of Nursing in Seattle, the Master of Science in Nursing engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-nursing-practice-prof': 'Nursing is a health care profession that "integrates the art and science of caring and focuses on the protection, promotion, and optimization of health and human functioning; prevention of illness and injury; facilitation of healing; and alleviation of suffering through compassionate presence". At the University of Washington\'s School of Nursing in Seattle, the Doctor of Nursing Practice engages this discipline at the professional level.',
    'uw-nursing-phd': 'Doctoral research. Nursing is a health care profession that "integrates the art and science of caring and focuses on the protection, promotion, and optimization of health and human functioning; prevention of illness and injury; facilitation of healing; and alleviation of suffering through compassionate presence". At the University of Washington\'s School of Nursing in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Nursing engages this discipline at the doctoral level.',
    'uw-biomedical-regulatory-affairs-ms': "Regulatory affairs (RA), is a profession that deals with an organization’s adherence to regulatory compliance. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Master of Science in Biomedical Regulatory Affairs engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-health-economics-and-outcomes-research-ms': "Graduate study. Health economics is a branch of economics concerned with issues related to efficiency, effectiveness, value and behavior in the production and consumption of health and healthcare. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Master of Science in Health Economics and Outcomes Research engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-medicinal-chemistry-ms': "Graduate study. Medicinal or pharmaceutical chemistry is a scientific discipline at the intersection of chemistry and pharmacy involved with designing and developing pharmaceutical drugs. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Master of Science in Medicinal Chemistry engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-pharmaceutics-ms': "Graduate study. Pharmaceutics is the discipline of pharmacy that deals with the process of turning a new chemical entity (NCE) or an existing drug into a medication to be used safely and effectively by patients. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Master of Science in Pharmaceutics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-pharmacy-prof': "Pharmacy is the science and practice of discovering, producing, preparing, dispensing, reviewing and monitoring medications, aiming to ensure the safe, effective, and affordable use of medicines. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Doctor of Pharmacy engages this discipline at the professional level.",
    'uw-health-economics-and-outcomes-research-phd': "Doctoral research. Health economics is a branch of economics concerned with issues related to efficiency, effectiveness, value and behavior in the production and consumption of health and healthcare. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Health Economics and Outcomes Research engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-medicinal-chemistry-phd': "Doctoral research. Medicinal or pharmaceutical chemistry is a scientific discipline at the intersection of chemistry and pharmacy involved with designing and developing pharmaceutical drugs. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Medicinal Chemistry engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-pharmaceutics-phd': "Doctoral research. Pharmaceutics is the discipline of pharmacy that deals with the process of turning a new chemical entity (NCE) or an existing drug into a medication to be used safely and effectively by patients. At the University of Washington's School of Pharmacy in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Pharmaceutics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-public-service-and-policy-bs': "Public administration, also known as public policy and administration or public management, is the implementation of public policies, which are sets of proposed or decided actions to solve problems and address relevant social and economic issues. At the University of Washington's Daniel J. Evans School of Public Policy and Governance in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Public Service and Policy engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-public-administration-ms': "Public administration, also known as public policy and administration or public management, is the implementation of public policies, which are sets of proposed or decided actions to solve problems and address relevant social and economic issues. At the University of Washington's Daniel J. Evans School of Public Policy and Governance in Seattle, the Master of Science in Public Administration engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-public-policy-and-management-ms': "Graduate study. Public policy is an institutionalized proposal or a decided set of elements like laws, regulations, guidelines, and actions to solve or address relevant and problematic social issues, guided by a conception and often implemented by programs. At the University of Washington's Daniel J. Evans School of Public Policy and Governance in Seattle, the Master of Science in Public Policy & Management engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-public-policy-and-management-phd': "Doctoral research. Public policy is an institutionalized proposal or a decided set of elements like laws, regulations, guidelines, and actions to solve or address relevant and problematic social issues, guided by a conception and often implemented by programs. At the University of Washington's Daniel J. Evans School of Public Policy and Governance in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Public Policy & Management engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-environmental-public-health-bs': "Its study determines the requirements for a healthy environment, with the goal of effective control over the factors that affect health. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Environmental Public Health engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-food-systems-nutrition-and-health-bs': "Nutrition is the biochemical and physiological process by which an organism uses food and water to support its life. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Food Systems, Nutrition, and Health engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-public-health-global-health-bs': 'Public health is "the science of preventing disease, prolonging life and promoting health through the organized efforts and informed choices of society, organizations, public and private, communities and individuals". At the University of Washington\'s School of Public Health in Seattle, the Bachelor of Science in Public Health-Global Health engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.',
    'uw-biostatistics-ms': "Graduate study. Biostatistics is a branch of statistics that applies statistical methods to a wide range of topics in the biological sciences, with a focus on clinical medicine and public health applications. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Biostatistics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-environmental-health-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. Environmental health is the branch of public health concerned with all aspects of the natural and built environment affecting human health. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Environmental Health Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-epidemiology-ms': "Graduate study. Epidemiology is the study and analysis of the distribution, patterns and determinants of health and disease conditions in a defined population, and application of this knowledge to prevent diseases. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Epidemiology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-genetic-epidemiology-ms': "Genetic epidemiology is the study of the role of genetic factors in determining health and disease in families and in populations, and the interplay of such genetic factors with environmental factors. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Genetic Epidemiology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-global-health-ms': 'Global health is the health of populations in a worldwide context; it has been defined as "the area of study, research, and practice that places a priority on improving health and achieving equity in health for all people worldwide". At the University of Washington\'s School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Global Health engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-health-administration-ms': "Health administration, healthcare administration, healthcare management, health services management or hospital management is the field relating to leadership, management, and administration of public health systems, health care systems, hospitals, and hospital networks in all the primary, secondary, and tertiary secto. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Health Administration engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-health-informatics-and-health-information-management-ms': "It can be viewed as a branch of engineering and applied science. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Health Informatics & Health Information Management engages this discipline at the master's level. The program is offered fully online.",
    'uw-health-systems-and-population-health-ms': 'Population health has been defined as "the health outcomes of a group of individuals, including the distribution of such outcomes within the group". At the University of Washington\'s School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Health Systems and Population Health engages this discipline at the master\'s level.',
    'uw-nutritional-sciences-ms': "Graduate study. The intake of these substances provides organisms with nutrients which can be metabolized to create energy and chemical structures; too much or too little of an essential nutrient can cause malnutrition. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Nutritional Sciences engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-pathobiology-ms': "Graduate study. Pathology is the study of disease. The word pathology also refers to the study of disease in general, incorporating a wide range of biology research fields and medical practices. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Pathobiology engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-public-health-genetics-ms': "Graduate study. Public health genomics is the use of genomics information to benefit public health. This is visualized as more effective preventive care and disease treatments with better specificity, tailored to the genetic makeup of each patient. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Public Health Genetics engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-public-health-nutrition-ms': "Public Health Nutrition is a monthly peer-reviewed public health journal covering nutrition-related public health topics. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Master of Science in Public Health Nutrition engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-biostatistics-phd': "Doctoral research. Biostatistics is a branch of statistics that applies statistical methods to a wide range of topics in the biological sciences, with a focus on clinical medicine and public health applications. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Biostatistics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-environmental-health-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. Environmental health is the branch of public health concerned with all aspects of the natural and built environment affecting human health. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Environmental Health Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-epidemiology-phd': "Doctoral research. Epidemiology is the study and analysis of the distribution, patterns and determinants of health and disease conditions in a defined population, and application of this knowledge to prevent diseases. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Epidemiology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-global-health-global-health-metrics-and-implementation-sciences-phd': "Implementation research is the systematic study of methods that support the application of research findings and other evidence-based knowledge into policy and practice. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Global Health: Global Health Metrics & Implementation Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-health-services-phd': "Health care, or healthcare, is the improvement or maintenance of health via the prevention, diagnosis, treatment, amelioration or cure of disease, illness, injury, and other physical and mental impairments in people. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Health Services engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-nutritional-sciences-phd': "Doctoral research. The intake of these substances provides organisms with nutrients which can be metabolized to create energy and chemical structures; too much or too little of an essential nutrient can cause malnutrition. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Nutritional Sciences engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-pathobiology-phd': "Doctoral research. Pathology is the study of disease. The word pathology also refers to the study of disease in general, incorporating a wide range of biology research fields and medical practices. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Pathobiology engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-public-health-genetics-phd': "Doctoral research. Public health genomics is the use of genomics information to benefit public health. This is visualized as more effective preventive care and disease treatments with better specificity, tailored to the genetic makeup of each patient. At the University of Washington's School of Public Health in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Public Health Genetics engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
    'uw-social-welfare-bs': "Welfare spending is a type of government support intended to ensure that members of a society can meet basic human needs such as food and shelter. At the University of Washington's School of Social Work in Seattle, the Bachelor of Arts in Social Welfare engages this discipline at the undergraduate level.",
    'uw-social-work-ms': "Social work is an academic discipline and practice-based profession concerned with meeting the basic needs of individuals, families, groups, communities, and society as a whole to enhance their individual and collective well-being. At the University of Washington's School of Social Work in Seattle, the Master of Science in Social Work engages this discipline at the master's level.",
    'uw-social-welfare-phd': "Doctoral research. Welfare spending is a type of government support intended to ensure that members of a society can meet basic human needs such as food and shelter. At the University of Washington's School of Social Work in Seattle, the Doctor of Philosophy in Social Welfare engages this discipline at the doctoral level.",
}

